WEBVTT

00:02.219 --> 00:03.612
- It's just, I don't understand
why they didn't do it.

00:03.655 --> 00:05.483
I don't know what's
the matter with these people.

00:05.527 --> 00:07.311
You know what, I don't
understand why they can't just

00:07.355 --> 00:09.270
call us and tell
us the chef has COVID

00:09.313 --> 00:10.314
before we drive
all the way out there.

00:10.358 --> 00:12.316
- Okay, honey, relax.

00:12.360 --> 00:13.665
- Waste of our entire night.

00:13.709 --> 00:15.058
- Okay, well,
we still have plenty

00:15.102 --> 00:16.755
of time to turn it around.

00:16.799 --> 00:18.235
Okay?

00:18.279 --> 00:20.672
You don't have to be
so stressed all the time.

00:30.204 --> 00:32.119
What's that?

00:32.162 --> 00:33.642
Is someone outside?

00:33.685 --> 00:36.645
[tense music]

00:36.688 --> 00:41.737
♪

00:41.780 --> 00:42.738
- Stay here.

00:42.781 --> 00:44.435
- Will--
- Stay here.

00:52.878 --> 00:54.619
- Lupe?

00:54.663 --> 00:56.752
Victor?

00:56.795 --> 00:58.232
Is that my money bag?

00:58.275 --> 00:59.711
What are you doing
with our money bag?

00:59.755 --> 01:01.844
Are you trying to rob us?

01:01.887 --> 01:03.585
No, you do not--
get out of the car.

01:03.628 --> 01:05.195
Take that bag out.

01:05.239 --> 01:06.370
Get that bag out of the car.

01:06.414 --> 01:08.329
Get out of the car, Victor!

01:08.372 --> 01:09.504
Get out of the car!

01:09.547 --> 01:11.375
- Victor, drive!
- Are you kidding me?

01:11.419 --> 01:12.463
Get out of that car!

01:12.507 --> 01:14.378
I need that money, Victor!

01:22.430 --> 01:24.562
It's Lupe and Victor.
- What?

01:24.606 --> 01:26.477
- It's Lupe and Victor,
they're trying to rob us.

01:26.521 --> 01:28.436
They got our money, go, go.
- Right.

01:30.612 --> 01:31.917
Why?
- Trying to steal our money.

01:31.961 --> 01:33.702
- All of it?
- I don't know.

01:33.745 --> 01:34.920
They had the bag,
they put it in the van.

01:34.964 --> 01:36.183
I just saw them
coming out of the barn.

01:36.226 --> 01:39.490
♪

01:39.534 --> 01:41.579
Faster, faster, faster.

01:41.623 --> 01:43.320
Get on them, come on,
stay on them.

01:43.364 --> 01:44.713
Don't let them get away--
- Okay!

01:44.756 --> 01:46.410
- Go faster.
- I'm trying.

01:48.325 --> 01:51.198
- They're still after us--
[speaking Spanish]

01:52.677 --> 01:54.766
- They're turning.
- I can see that.

01:54.810 --> 01:56.899
- It's the cutoff to the
freeway, he's headed to Canada.

01:56.942 --> 01:58.466
We go straight,
we can cut them off.

02:01.730 --> 02:03.688
[both speaking Spanish]

02:06.822 --> 02:08.171
- We did it.
- We have to get out of here.

02:08.215 --> 02:13.568
♪

02:13.611 --> 02:14.743
- There they are.

02:16.875 --> 02:18.138
- Victor, is that him?

02:19.400 --> 02:21.445
I see him. Victor that's them!
- No, no.

02:21.489 --> 02:22.968
- Victor, yes it--
yes it is, Victor!

02:23.012 --> 02:24.405
- What are you doing?
Slow down.

02:24.448 --> 02:25.928
Slow down, slow down!
- That's them, Vic, go, go!

02:27.321 --> 02:28.278
[screaming]

02:28.322 --> 02:35.329
♪

03:03.400 --> 03:04.619
- Help!

03:16.413 --> 03:17.980
- You tried to screw us,
Victor.

03:18.023 --> 03:22.376
- Mr. Will, we needed
to get back to our children.

03:22.419 --> 03:24.029
I'm sorry, Mr. Will.

03:24.073 --> 03:25.944
- Will!

03:25.988 --> 03:27.642
It's ruined.

03:27.685 --> 03:28.773
It's all gone.

03:28.817 --> 03:32.255
- I'm sorry.
I'm sorry, Mr. Will.

03:32.299 --> 03:33.474
Mr. Will.

03:33.517 --> 03:34.736
No, no!

03:34.779 --> 03:35.998
- I'm sorry.

03:36.041 --> 03:37.869
We just--we just
wanted out, please.

03:37.913 --> 03:40.524
We can make this right--
[gunshots]

03:40.568 --> 03:43.614
- [screaming and crying]

03:46.617 --> 03:49.577
Mr. Will, I'm sorry--
Mr.--no!

03:49.620 --> 03:51.013
- Oh, my God.

03:51.056 --> 03:52.623
- I had to do it.

03:52.667 --> 03:54.582
They betrayed us,
and they stole from us--

03:54.625 --> 03:55.844
- I know, okay, just--

03:55.887 --> 03:58.281
- [groans]

03:58.325 --> 03:59.674
- What was that?

04:02.633 --> 04:04.374
- [coughing]

04:04.418 --> 04:05.984
- Who are they?
- I don't know.

04:06.028 --> 04:07.290
- Okay,
we gotta get out of here.

04:07.334 --> 04:08.813
- How? Our car's totaled.

04:08.857 --> 04:10.685
- We can't just leave her.
We have to go back for Rachel.

04:10.728 --> 04:11.686
- It's too risky.

04:11.729 --> 04:13.122
- No, we don't have a choice!

04:13.165 --> 04:15.603
Look, we said we wanted out,
and now is our chance.

04:15.646 --> 04:17.344
Okay, we'll take the trail
through the park,

04:17.387 --> 04:19.868
grab the truck from the barn,
get Rachel, and go.

04:19.911 --> 04:21.043
It's the only way.

04:24.438 --> 04:25.917
What are you doing?

04:25.961 --> 04:27.789
- I'm finishing the job.

04:27.832 --> 04:30.400
- No, no. No.

04:30.444 --> 04:32.402
[gunshots]

04:32.446 --> 04:39.453
♪

04:50.507 --> 04:53.336
- I don't know how
many times Anais's school

04:53.380 --> 04:56.774
has asked me for her
walking field trip waiver--

04:56.818 --> 04:58.602
- Charlotte was
supposed to take care of it.

04:58.646 --> 05:00.082
- I'll talk to her.

05:00.125 --> 05:02.954
Looks like Theo's
enjoying his breakfast.

05:02.998 --> 05:04.521
What do you and Charlotte want?

05:04.565 --> 05:05.566
- I don't even know if
Charlotte

05:05.609 --> 05:07.045
eats breakfast anymore.

05:07.089 --> 05:09.570
- Okay.

05:09.613 --> 05:10.919
What is going on?

05:10.962 --> 05:12.573
- Every day, when I get up,
she's gone.

05:12.616 --> 05:13.965
When I get home,
she's sleeping.

05:14.009 --> 05:16.533
It's like we're two
sleep-deprived ships

05:16.577 --> 05:17.839
passing in the night.

05:17.882 --> 05:20.494
- You're both under
so much stress at work.

05:20.537 --> 05:23.018
How's the team doing
now that Jess is gone?

05:23.061 --> 05:26.108
- It's so hard I can't
even tell how hard it is.

05:26.151 --> 05:27.892
- But we're
taking it day by day.

05:27.936 --> 05:31.679
No one wants to fill his shoes,
but we still have a job to do.

05:31.722 --> 05:34.638
And still no word from
Isobel on his replacement.

05:34.682 --> 05:36.988
- Ah, the unknown variable.

05:37.032 --> 05:38.903
Whole soup pot boiling away

05:38.947 --> 05:42.385
until that final ingredient
lands to infuse.

05:42.429 --> 05:43.952
- Now I'm getting hungry.

05:43.995 --> 05:45.867
- Want my advice?

05:45.910 --> 05:47.825
Stick with what you know.

05:47.869 --> 05:49.697
And you know a lot more
than you think.

05:49.740 --> 05:50.872
[phone dings]

05:52.874 --> 05:54.136
- Work.
- Ah.

05:54.179 --> 05:55.746
Come on.

05:55.790 --> 05:57.922
Oh, look at my baby.

05:57.966 --> 06:01.056
My little baby burrito.

06:01.099 --> 06:03.885
This is my
favorite time of the day.

06:03.928 --> 06:06.496
Where I get to talk
to you and tell you

06:06.540 --> 06:09.064
that I am gonna keep you safe.

06:10.674 --> 06:13.068
I love you.
- Love you.

06:13.111 --> 06:14.112
- Yes.

06:14.156 --> 06:15.723
We're gonna have
a good time today.

06:15.766 --> 06:17.551
- We've got two
suspected fugitives.

06:17.594 --> 06:18.943
State Police say the sedan
up there belongs

06:18.987 --> 06:21.032
to a Will and Marianne Conway.

06:21.076 --> 06:22.512
- That explains the two
sets of prints

06:22.556 --> 06:24.166
from the car to the van
then off into the woods.

06:24.209 --> 06:25.385
- It's a state park
back there.

06:25.428 --> 06:27.212
We already have
three dog teams looking.

06:27.256 --> 06:28.910
- So what do we know
about the Conways?

06:28.953 --> 06:31.956
- Married eleven years,
no kids, no criminal record.

06:32.000 --> 06:34.437
Will sells commercial real
estate, Marianne's a homemaker.

06:34.481 --> 06:36.047
They live 8 miles from here.

06:36.091 --> 06:37.832
- So why'd they kill
six people?

06:37.875 --> 06:39.660
- Could it be road rage
gone wrong?

06:39.703 --> 06:41.792
But does that warrant
killing six people point-blank?

06:41.836 --> 06:43.620
- Well, does it warrant us?

06:43.664 --> 06:46.057
- No, but suspected
human trafficking would.

06:46.101 --> 06:47.755
Four of the victims
are undocumented immigrants.

06:47.798 --> 06:49.147
The only two U.S. Citizens

06:49.191 --> 06:51.019
were the driver,
Victor Ruiz, and his wife Lupe.

06:51.062 --> 06:52.455
[phone rings]

06:52.499 --> 06:54.762
Last known in New Mexico,
where Victor worked

06:54.805 --> 06:55.937
as a ranch foreman
before they both

06:55.980 --> 06:57.417
disappeared off the grid
last year.

06:57.460 --> 07:00.202
- Well, between that
and this barbecued bag of cash,

07:00.245 --> 07:01.638
the Ruizes might be coyotes,

07:01.682 --> 07:03.640
smuggling people
across the Canadian border.

07:03.684 --> 07:05.033
- So how do we know
the Conways were involved

07:05.076 --> 07:06.208
in human trafficking?

07:06.251 --> 07:07.557
- Right now, we don't.

07:07.601 --> 07:09.167
- Park Police got a
stolen vehicle report.

07:09.211 --> 07:10.691
A couple of kids
went camping last night.

07:10.734 --> 07:11.909
When they got back
to their parking lot

07:11.953 --> 07:13.824
in Sycamore Falls,
their car was gone.

07:13.868 --> 07:15.086
Witness saw a man
and a woman prowling

07:15.130 --> 07:16.740
around the lot
early this morning.

07:16.784 --> 07:18.263
- Was it the Conways?

07:18.307 --> 07:19.613
- Could be. I'll check it out.

07:19.656 --> 07:20.657
Could you send me
those pictures?

07:20.701 --> 07:22.485
- Yeah, I'll send them.

07:22.529 --> 07:23.660
- Agent Gibson.

07:23.704 --> 07:27.708
Uh-huh. Yeah, thanks.

07:27.751 --> 07:29.100
County got a 911 call.

07:29.144 --> 07:30.754
The Conways never
came home last night.

07:30.798 --> 07:32.277
- From who?
- Their nanny.

07:32.321 --> 07:33.670
- How does that work?

07:33.714 --> 07:35.150
I thought they didn't
have kids?

07:35.193 --> 07:38.806
[suspenseful music]

07:38.849 --> 07:40.764
- Dan and Marianne go
on date nights all the time,

07:40.808 --> 07:42.592
but they always come home
so they can see Rachel

07:42.636 --> 07:43.985
first thing in the morning.

07:44.028 --> 07:45.943
But I called the police,
not the FBI,

07:45.987 --> 07:47.945
so why would you--

07:47.989 --> 07:50.078
wha-what's going on?

07:50.121 --> 07:52.123
- There was an accident
last night.

07:52.167 --> 07:53.516
- Oh, no.

07:53.560 --> 07:54.604
- And we don't know
exactly what happened,

07:54.648 --> 07:55.736
but we know
that they're missing.

07:55.779 --> 07:56.954
- Do you know
where they could be?

07:56.998 --> 07:58.739
- No, last I talked
to them they were

07:58.782 --> 08:00.131
leaving for the restaurant.

08:00.175 --> 08:02.090
- Where are my mama and papa?

08:02.133 --> 08:04.135
- Rachel, sweetie--
- No, it's okay.

08:04.179 --> 08:06.224
- Hi, Rachel. Hi.

08:06.268 --> 08:07.617
I'm Sheryll.

08:07.661 --> 08:09.750
I have a daughter,
and she has exactly

08:09.793 --> 08:11.273
the same bunny as you.

08:11.316 --> 08:12.970
- You squeeze it,
and it sniffs.

08:13.014 --> 08:15.103
- I know, I know.

08:15.146 --> 08:16.974
I'm sure your mama
and papa are fine.

08:17.018 --> 08:18.193
We're looking for them too.

08:18.236 --> 08:20.543
Do you have any idea
where they could be?

08:20.587 --> 08:23.111
Friends' house
or an ice cream store?

08:23.154 --> 08:24.765
- Maybe the farm.

08:24.808 --> 08:27.158
- I never heard them talk
about any farm.

08:27.202 --> 08:28.638
- Where's this farm?

08:28.682 --> 08:31.772
- My mama used to say
"Don't worry, bunny cat,

08:31.815 --> 08:33.904
we'll be right
under your nose."

08:35.123 --> 08:36.559
Where is she?

08:36.603 --> 08:40.824
[sentimental music]

08:40.868 --> 08:42.173
- Guess I've lost my touch.

08:42.217 --> 08:44.088
- No, you were
great with her.

08:44.132 --> 08:46.264
- Ortiz says the car
the Conways stole

08:46.308 --> 08:47.831
was a Jeep Grand Cherokee.

08:47.875 --> 08:49.180
The BOLO's already out.

08:49.224 --> 08:50.791
- Well, if this
isn't human trafficking,

08:50.834 --> 08:52.270
how do we know no one's coming
for the nanny or for Rachel?

08:52.314 --> 08:54.316
- Exactly--I'll get
state police here

08:54.359 --> 08:56.579
and wait till they escort them
somewhere safe.

08:56.623 --> 08:58.102
Why don't you two see
if you can find this farm?

08:58.146 --> 08:59.582
Sounds like it could be close.

08:59.626 --> 09:01.845
- I mean, if it's even real.
She's just a child.

09:01.889 --> 09:07.634
♪

09:07.677 --> 09:10.637
[suspenseful music]

09:10.680 --> 09:13.727
♪

09:13.770 --> 09:16.643
- There she is. My baby girl.

09:16.686 --> 09:18.732
- The FBI
already knows about her.

09:18.775 --> 09:20.298
They'll be able to protect her.

09:20.342 --> 09:21.691
- She needs her mother, Will.

09:21.735 --> 09:22.910
- And she'll have her.

09:22.953 --> 09:25.652
If we let the FBI
keep her safe from them.

09:25.695 --> 09:27.305
You said it yourself,
we want to get away,

09:27.349 --> 09:28.829
and now we've got our chance.

09:28.872 --> 09:30.613
Let's get across
the border to Canada,

09:30.657 --> 09:32.615
lay low for a little while,
and we'll come back for her

09:32.659 --> 09:34.661
when the heat dies down.

09:39.230 --> 09:40.623
- I'll give it a week.

09:40.667 --> 09:42.886
And then we either
come back for Rachel together,

09:42.930 --> 09:44.888
or I come back alone.

09:44.932 --> 09:46.411
I'm not leaving her.

09:46.455 --> 09:48.196
No matter what.

09:48.239 --> 09:50.328
- Okay. Let's go.

09:50.372 --> 09:52.113
- First we need
our insurance policy.

09:54.985 --> 09:56.117
- You sure?

09:59.207 --> 10:00.208
- Come on.

10:03.428 --> 10:05.996
- Going to be
a big girl, yeah?

10:06.040 --> 10:07.694
- Wanna go to my house?

10:07.737 --> 10:08.912
Okay.

10:08.956 --> 10:15.745
♪

10:23.927 --> 10:26.277
- Hey, has Sheryll seemed
a little off to you lately?

10:26.321 --> 10:29.106
- Yeah, it's the
maternity leave thing.

10:29.150 --> 10:30.847
She didn't talk to you?

10:30.891 --> 10:33.023
She's worried about
watching Theo grow up,

10:33.067 --> 10:35.678
and her wife wants her to
stay home, but I don't know,

10:35.722 --> 10:37.419
she doesn't want
to abandon the team.

10:37.462 --> 10:39.203
- Well, it's not abandoning us,
it's taking care of her family.

10:39.247 --> 10:40.857
- That's what I said to her.

10:40.901 --> 10:42.032
- When I had my son,

10:42.076 --> 10:44.687
I was back at work
a week later.

10:44.731 --> 10:48.299
I had my ex at home, but still,
I wish I'd taken the--

10:48.343 --> 10:49.953
taken the time.

10:49.997 --> 10:51.215
- You should tell her that.

10:51.259 --> 10:52.956
I know she wanted
to talk to you.

10:53.000 --> 10:55.829
She's nervous
to tell Isobel too.

10:55.872 --> 10:57.134
- Well, Isobel will understand.

10:57.178 --> 10:59.180
I think she'll respect her
all the more for it.

11:02.357 --> 11:04.925
- Is that a cellar door?

11:23.073 --> 11:24.379
- It looks like
a root cellar.

11:24.422 --> 11:27.382
[tense music]

11:27.425 --> 11:34.432
♪

11:38.045 --> 11:39.046
Clear.

11:40.395 --> 11:43.180
- Looks like two people
have been living here.

11:43.224 --> 11:44.965
Victor and Lupe, maybe?

11:45.008 --> 11:46.314
- Well, for what?

11:46.357 --> 11:48.359
Some kind
of human smuggling operation?

11:48.403 --> 11:54.322
♪

11:54.365 --> 11:57.020
- Or not human smuggling.

11:57.064 --> 11:58.761
The Conways were
exploiting them to run

11:58.805 --> 12:01.024
a grow operation--
probably selling too.

12:01.068 --> 12:03.331
- Six people killed,
a little girl abandoned,

12:03.374 --> 12:06.943
all for some small
grow farm in a legal state?

12:06.987 --> 12:09.293
- Yeah,
it doesn't make much sense.

12:13.210 --> 12:15.778
- Why-why's the door open?
- Doesn't matter.

12:15.822 --> 12:17.388
We got to get to that safe.

12:28.138 --> 12:30.793
- FBI, freeze!

12:30.837 --> 12:33.274
[gunshots]
[keypad beeping]

12:33.317 --> 12:34.362
- Go, go, go!

12:38.409 --> 12:39.367
Go, go, go, go.

12:39.410 --> 12:41.021
Come on, I'll cover you.

12:45.852 --> 12:47.375
Go, go, go!

12:49.072 --> 12:50.204
- Go, go, go, go!

12:53.990 --> 12:54.991
- Go!

13:02.346 --> 13:04.174
[both coughing]

13:04.218 --> 13:07.134
- Don't breathe so hard,
just cover your face.

13:07.177 --> 13:08.352
Cover your face.

13:15.142 --> 13:17.013
- Hurry up, get out!

13:17.057 --> 13:18.928
Quickly.

13:18.972 --> 13:20.321
I heard the gunfire.
Are you okay?

13:20.364 --> 13:21.452
- Yeah.

13:28.982 --> 13:30.070
- Okay. Yeah.

13:30.113 --> 13:32.899
Well, I appreciate it.
Thank you.

13:32.942 --> 13:33.900
- You guys sure
you're okay?

13:33.943 --> 13:35.292
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah.

13:35.336 --> 13:36.598
Anything on our fugitives?

13:36.641 --> 13:37.860
- Yeah,
tire tracks at the edge

13:37.904 --> 13:39.470
of the field match
the Cherokee they stole

13:39.514 --> 13:40.689
from the state park.

13:40.732 --> 13:43.431
PD lost the trail,
but the BOLO's still out.

13:43.474 --> 13:45.781
- Will and Marianne must have
known the FBI was on the scene,

13:45.825 --> 13:48.915
and they risked
coming back here anyway, why?

13:48.958 --> 13:50.438
- Marianne's a mother.

13:50.481 --> 13:51.918
Maybe she came back for Rachel
but changed course

13:51.961 --> 13:53.441
when she saw her with you?

13:53.484 --> 13:55.835
- Or maybe this.

14:00.100 --> 14:01.536
- So that's what
they came back for.

14:01.579 --> 14:03.625
- Before Will
opened fire to protect it.

14:03.668 --> 14:05.801
- Or to protect this.

14:05.845 --> 14:08.804
[suspenseful music]

14:08.848 --> 14:11.024
♪

14:11.067 --> 14:12.373
- Seeds.

14:12.416 --> 14:14.679
- And that must have been
what she was grabbing.

14:14.723 --> 14:17.073
- They blew off their daughter,
shot at two FBI agents,

14:17.117 --> 14:18.988
and let their marijuana crop
go up in smoke

14:19.032 --> 14:20.381
over a packet of seeds.

14:20.424 --> 14:22.426
- Well, whatever it is,
it's obviously valuable.

14:22.470 --> 14:24.776
- I'm going to get it sent
to the DEA lab in Manhattan,

14:24.820 --> 14:27.083
see if they can
tell us what's up.

14:27.127 --> 14:28.737
- The FBI's on our ass.

14:28.780 --> 14:30.478
Why aren't we
in the carpool lane to Canada?

14:30.521 --> 14:31.696
- We need money, Will.

14:31.740 --> 14:33.698
- We have the seeds.
- I mean fast cash.

14:33.742 --> 14:36.614
We can't use our credit cards,
can't write a check.

14:36.658 --> 14:38.486
But we can use them.

14:38.529 --> 14:41.532
[indistinct conversation]

14:43.795 --> 14:46.102
- You nailed it.

14:46.146 --> 14:49.497
Two ex-cons now benefitting
from what is no longer a crime.

14:49.540 --> 14:50.977
- Hey, thought you'd
appreciate that one.

14:51.020 --> 14:52.500
- I am so sorry to have
to tell you this, gentlemen,

14:52.543 --> 14:53.980
but the system is still rigged.

14:54.023 --> 14:54.981
Open that door.

14:55.024 --> 14:56.852
Now!

14:56.896 --> 14:59.855
[tense music]

14:59.899 --> 15:02.423
♪

15:02.466 --> 15:03.772
- Last year,
the Conways submitted

15:03.815 --> 15:05.600
an expedited application
for a license

15:05.643 --> 15:07.732
to legally sell pot in Vermont.

15:07.776 --> 15:09.996
- Why the sudden rush?
Pot was already legal here.

15:10.039 --> 15:11.998
- Yeah, to grow and to use,
but not to distribute,

15:12.041 --> 15:13.913
so when the state
finally did legalize sales,

15:13.956 --> 15:16.089
there was a rush to be
the first retail operator.

15:16.132 --> 15:18.700
The Conways paid
hefty application fees,

15:18.743 --> 15:20.093
funded environmental studies.

15:20.136 --> 15:21.572
They even signed an affidavit

15:21.616 --> 15:23.705
promising not to use harmful
pesticides on their crop,

15:23.748 --> 15:25.707
but their application
was still denied.

15:25.750 --> 15:26.708
- So now they've spent
all their money

15:26.751 --> 15:28.275
on a rejected application,

15:28.318 --> 15:30.407
yet they're still running
a grow operation in the cellar.

15:30.451 --> 15:32.670
- Question is, where did they
get the seed money?

15:32.714 --> 15:34.934
- Well, I've been going
through their financials.

15:34.977 --> 15:37.849
Every day, they get a bunch
of payments through cash apps.

15:37.893 --> 15:40.504
Marianne for dance school,
bake sales,

15:40.548 --> 15:42.071
guys paying Will back
for poker night.

15:42.115 --> 15:43.768
- Okay, and you think
these were payments

15:43.812 --> 15:45.553
for pot grown
and sold illegally?

15:45.596 --> 15:47.990
- Or an innovative way
to launder drug cash.

15:48.034 --> 15:49.992
- There's
another party involved?

15:50.036 --> 15:51.646
- I'm not sure yet.

15:51.689 --> 15:53.735
But once the money never stays
in the Conways' account long.

15:53.778 --> 15:55.519
It gets transferred
to an offshore account

15:55.563 --> 15:56.868
named "Marguerite Corp."

15:56.912 --> 15:58.566
- Belonging to Will
and Marianne.

15:58.609 --> 16:00.220
- I don't think so,
but whoever it is

16:00.263 --> 16:02.135
is making a cut of the profits.

16:02.178 --> 16:03.745
- Maybe a cartel.

16:03.788 --> 16:05.877
- Lab just sent over
the analysis for those seeds

16:05.921 --> 16:07.749
you got out
of the Conways' safe.

16:07.792 --> 16:10.578
They produce a highly valuable
and rare strain of Sativa,

16:10.621 --> 16:12.058
usually only grown in Colombia.

16:12.101 --> 16:14.060
- Yeah, but that crop didn't
look all that impressive,

16:14.103 --> 16:16.062
even before Will fire to it.

16:16.105 --> 16:17.977
- Either way,
they're worth dying for.

16:18.020 --> 16:20.501
- Or killing for,
if you're a pessimist.

16:20.544 --> 16:21.719
- Oh, another thing.

16:21.763 --> 16:23.547
I went through vital records.

16:23.591 --> 16:25.462
Marianne's
maiden name was Mercer.

16:25.506 --> 16:28.552
She has a sister named
Laura Mercer in Middlebury.

16:28.596 --> 16:29.858
[phone dings]
- Okay, let's go talk to Laura,

16:29.901 --> 16:31.816
see if she's heard
from Will and Marianne.

16:33.862 --> 16:35.603
- LPR just picked up
the stolen Cherokee

16:35.646 --> 16:38.040
outside of a dispensary
in downtown Montpelier

16:38.084 --> 16:39.215
called Take You Higher.

16:39.259 --> 16:40.695
Local PD is on the scene.

16:40.738 --> 16:42.001
- I'll drive.

16:45.656 --> 16:47.180
- There must be some mistake.

16:47.223 --> 16:48.529
- I know this is difficult,

16:48.572 --> 16:50.096
but has Marianne
tried to contact you?

16:50.139 --> 16:53.055
- No, she wouldn't.
I work so much.

16:53.099 --> 16:54.578
- You're a professor?

16:54.622 --> 16:56.885
Yes, of Germanic and Slavic

16:56.928 --> 17:00.106
languages and literature
at Middlebury.

17:00.149 --> 17:03.848
I tend to lose myself
in my work.

17:03.892 --> 17:06.590
Which is why it pains me
to say that

17:06.634 --> 17:09.202
I haven't seen Marianne
for years.

17:09.245 --> 17:12.118
Maybe if I'd seen her,
I could have noticed

17:12.161 --> 17:15.599
that she was going down
a bad path, but I never

17:15.643 --> 17:18.994
kept a good eye on her the way
a big sister should.

17:19.038 --> 17:21.127
I knew that
my father adored her,

17:21.170 --> 17:24.521
they were close,
and I guess that let me

17:24.565 --> 17:26.567
escape into my books.

17:26.610 --> 17:27.959
- We're doing
everything we can

17:28.003 --> 17:29.744
to try to find your sister,
and in the meantime,

17:29.787 --> 17:31.615
rest assured
your niece is safe.

17:31.659 --> 17:33.052
- Oh, thank God.

17:33.095 --> 17:35.097
The poor girl.

17:35.141 --> 17:37.012
- Rachel is safe
with her nanny for now,

17:37.056 --> 17:40.798
but you are your sister's
next of kin.

17:40.842 --> 17:44.063
- If you want
to get custody of Rachel,

17:44.106 --> 17:45.325
we're happy to put you
in contact

17:45.368 --> 17:46.935
with people who can help.

17:46.978 --> 17:48.893
- I never had any children.

17:48.937 --> 17:51.200
When we were little,
Marianne set fire

17:51.244 --> 17:53.550
to the stove when I was
supposed to be watching her.

17:53.594 --> 17:56.118
I was reading a book,
oblivious.

17:56.162 --> 17:59.600
- You were a child yourself.

17:59.643 --> 18:02.603
- The truth is,
I haven't seen Marianne

18:02.646 --> 18:05.693
for so long that
I've never met Rachel.

18:05.736 --> 18:09.044
And the poor girl,
she must be so frightened.

18:09.088 --> 18:10.306
Don't you think it would be
better for her

18:10.350 --> 18:12.178
to stay with her nanny?

18:12.221 --> 18:13.744
[sentimental music]

18:13.788 --> 18:15.224
Just to give her
some consistency

18:15.268 --> 18:17.748
while this disaster
is resolved?

18:21.100 --> 18:22.231
- I understand.

18:22.275 --> 18:23.928
We've laid a lot on you.

18:25.626 --> 18:28.107
If Marianne does try
to get in contact with you,

18:28.150 --> 18:29.238
please let me know.

18:30.979 --> 18:32.720
Thank you.

18:32.763 --> 18:39.683
♪

18:39.727 --> 18:41.903
- Thank you.

18:41.946 --> 18:44.732
Detective, Agent Gaines.

18:44.775 --> 18:46.734
This is Agent Ortiz.
- Glad you're here.

18:46.777 --> 18:49.215
- Saw our fugitives'
stolen Cherokee outside.

18:49.258 --> 18:51.217
- That's not all
they left behind.

19:00.051 --> 19:01.401
- These are
the shop owners?

19:01.444 --> 19:03.925
- Yeah, Raymont Griffiths
and his brother Rodney.

19:03.968 --> 19:05.753
Both served time
for marijuana possession

19:05.796 --> 19:07.755
before Vermont legalized pot.

19:07.798 --> 19:09.191
Governor commuted
their sentences,

19:09.235 --> 19:11.628
and the state ended up
granting them the license

19:11.672 --> 19:13.935
for the first retail dispensary
in Vermont.

19:13.978 --> 19:15.066
- They turned
their lives around

19:15.110 --> 19:17.721
and never got
to see opening day.

19:17.765 --> 19:19.636
- Will and Marianne
applied for the same license

19:19.680 --> 19:20.898
these two were granted.

19:20.942 --> 19:22.683
You thinking this is
a revenge killing?

19:22.726 --> 19:24.119
- Actually,
we're thinking robbery.

19:24.163 --> 19:25.816
- Why's that?

19:25.860 --> 19:28.819
[suspenseful music]

19:28.863 --> 19:30.256
♪

19:30.299 --> 19:32.301
Looks like Will and
Marianne stole their supply.

19:32.345 --> 19:35.957
- Take You Higher had two vans
registered to the business.

19:36.000 --> 19:37.785
- ERT found two sets of tire
tracks.

19:37.828 --> 19:39.003
They took both vans.

19:39.047 --> 19:41.136
- BOLO's gone out.
I'll check on it now.

19:41.180 --> 19:42.877
- Thank you.

19:42.920 --> 19:44.400
- They fill each van up
with wares,

19:44.444 --> 19:45.967
and they split up, why?

19:46.010 --> 19:47.447
- Well, more wares
equals more cash.

19:47.490 --> 19:49.710
And two vans are harder
to find than one.

19:49.753 --> 19:51.233
Only question is,
where do you offload

19:51.277 --> 19:52.756
two van-loads of pot,
and quick?

19:52.800 --> 19:55.324
- I read a DEA bulletin
last month about legal growers

19:55.368 --> 19:58.109
that make tons of cash
on motel sales in states

19:58.153 --> 19:59.720
where recreational pot
is still illegal.

19:59.763 --> 20:00.982
- So what are the
closest state lines

20:01.025 --> 20:02.331
where recreational
pot's illegal?

20:02.375 --> 20:04.072
[phones ringing]
- New York and New Hampshire.

20:06.292 --> 20:07.684
- And there you go.

20:07.728 --> 20:08.990
One of the Take You Higher Vans

20:09.033 --> 20:10.296
just crossed state line
into New Hampshire.

20:10.339 --> 20:12.341
- We gotta find
the closest motel on I-89.

20:12.385 --> 20:14.343
- Let's figure it out
on the way.

20:19.130 --> 20:20.349
- We would have made
it better if Vermont

20:20.393 --> 20:21.785
had given us the license.

20:21.829 --> 20:23.265
- We have something
much more valuable.

20:23.309 --> 20:24.919
Our insurance policy.

20:24.962 --> 20:28.096
An insurance policy
means nothing without Rachel.

20:28.139 --> 20:30.403
[knock at door]

20:30.446 --> 20:32.448
- Will and Marianne Conway!

20:34.058 --> 20:36.060
FBI! Open the door!

20:36.104 --> 20:39.063
[tense music]

20:39.107 --> 20:41.892
♪

20:41.936 --> 20:43.329
- Don't move!
Get on your knees!

20:43.372 --> 20:44.895
- Don't shoot!
- Get on your knees!

20:44.939 --> 20:46.070
Hands behind your head!

20:46.114 --> 20:47.202
- Don't shoot!
- Hands behind your head!

20:47.246 --> 20:48.334
- Don't shoot, please!

20:48.377 --> 20:49.639
Please, please,
please don't shoot!

20:49.683 --> 20:50.988
- Where's Will and Marianne?
- I don't know.

20:51.032 --> 20:52.163
- Why's their van
parked outside?

20:52.207 --> 20:53.208
- I--I--

20:53.252 --> 20:54.731
- Put your hands
back on your head.

20:56.385 --> 20:59.258
- Hey, drop the phone!
Put the phone down!

21:00.955 --> 21:02.304
Hey, drop the gun,
I don't want to--

21:02.348 --> 21:04.263
[gunshot]
No! No!

21:04.306 --> 21:10.269
♪

21:15.317 --> 21:16.623
- I can't believe
my wife is gone.

21:16.666 --> 21:18.538
- Why would she kill herself,
Michael?

21:20.366 --> 21:22.846
- Because the only thing she
was more afraid of than them

21:22.890 --> 21:24.500
was prison.

21:24.544 --> 21:27.024
They took everything
I care about.

21:27.068 --> 21:28.374
- Will and Marianne?

21:29.723 --> 21:31.855
Why were you driving
their stolen dispensary van?

21:31.899 --> 21:33.248
- Because Julie
and I worked for them,

21:33.292 --> 21:34.771
and they told us
to meet them there.

21:34.815 --> 21:36.773
- And what happened
when you got to the dispensary?

21:36.817 --> 21:38.862
- They told us the plan
was to rob the place,

21:38.906 --> 21:40.081
split up, and sell the product.

21:40.124 --> 21:41.561
- Then how did two people
end up murdered?

21:41.604 --> 21:42.562
- I swear,
Julie and I didn't know

21:42.605 --> 21:44.259
they were gonna kill anyone.

21:44.303 --> 21:47.349
- But they did, and you stayed.

21:47.393 --> 21:48.568
Why?

21:49.830 --> 21:52.746
- Because they told us that
if we did this one last job,

21:52.789 --> 21:55.357
sold the product,
they'd let us out.

21:55.401 --> 21:57.272
- Out of what?

21:57.316 --> 21:59.361
- Our obligation.

21:59.405 --> 22:02.756
They financed our first
illegal grow interest free.

22:02.799 --> 22:06.020
- So we're talking multi-level
marijuana marketing?

22:06.063 --> 22:09.502
- Yeah, if not hitting
your sales quota every month

22:09.545 --> 22:12.069
means scary dudes showing up

22:12.113 --> 22:13.680
and beating the crap out
of your wife

22:13.723 --> 22:15.682
while they make you watch.

22:15.725 --> 22:17.292
- They did that to you?

22:17.336 --> 22:21.427
- I-I let it happen.

22:21.470 --> 22:22.819
To Julie.

22:22.863 --> 22:24.560
[solemn music]

22:24.604 --> 22:27.694
I was too scared to fight.

22:27.737 --> 22:30.000
We wanted out...

22:30.044 --> 22:32.002
but couldn't figure out a way.

22:32.046 --> 22:33.482
Until...

22:37.791 --> 22:39.967
She knew I couldn't save her.

22:43.536 --> 22:44.537
- We believe you.

22:46.495 --> 22:47.583
Where are they now?

22:47.627 --> 22:48.932
- I don't know.

22:48.976 --> 22:50.673
All they said was,
meet them in Newport

22:50.717 --> 22:52.893
near the Canadian border.

22:52.936 --> 22:54.721
And then we'd never
have to work for them again.

23:00.466 --> 23:03.077
- I got access Julie's phone.
It's a burner.

23:03.120 --> 23:04.426
- You said she
was texting someone

23:04.470 --> 23:05.645
right before
she killed herself?

23:05.688 --> 23:06.950
- Yeah, it's right here.

23:06.994 --> 23:09.431
[suspenseful music]

23:09.475 --> 23:11.651
- She was warning Will
and Marianne.

23:14.131 --> 23:16.395
- Julie's text must have gone
through to Will and Marianne.

23:16.438 --> 23:18.440
They never went to Newport
or the border.

23:18.484 --> 23:20.007
They carjacked a man at a motel

23:20.050 --> 23:21.661
near the New York/Vermont
state line.

23:21.704 --> 23:24.446
Here's the
security cam footage.

23:24.490 --> 23:26.666
- Ram pickup.
Was there a GPS onboard?

23:26.709 --> 23:28.450
- I'm not sure,
but I put a BOLO out.

23:32.193 --> 23:34.804
- Hana,
were you up all night again?

23:34.848 --> 23:36.066
- Yes.

23:36.110 --> 23:37.459
I mean, one connection
just led to another,

23:37.503 --> 23:38.504
and I couldn't stop.

23:38.547 --> 23:39.940
I started
with Will and Marianne.

23:39.983 --> 23:41.637
Weirdly, their daughter Rachel

23:41.681 --> 23:42.812
doesn't have
a birth certificate

23:42.856 --> 23:45.119
or school records
or medical records.

23:45.162 --> 23:47.730
It's like they don't want
the world to know she exists.

23:47.774 --> 23:48.992
Which then led me
to realize that it's like

23:49.036 --> 23:50.559
the middle ages
here in Vermont.

23:50.603 --> 23:52.474
A lot of their vital records
haven't been digitized

23:52.518 --> 23:55.695
pre-2010, so there's not much
on Will and Marianne either.

23:55.738 --> 23:57.827
- So what does that mean?
- It's analog.

23:57.871 --> 24:00.134
A lot of it's stored in some
musty courthouse basement.

24:00.177 --> 24:02.441
I did have better luck with the
Marguerite Corporation, though.

24:02.484 --> 24:03.790
- Okay, what did you find?

24:03.833 --> 24:05.139
- Well, it's a vast web
of smaller

24:05.182 --> 24:06.880
shell corporations
like we suspected.

24:06.923 --> 24:10.710
These shell corporations
make up this illegal pot empire

24:10.753 --> 24:12.625
that runs a large swath
of New England.

24:12.668 --> 24:14.888
- And did you find out who Will
and Marianne are working for?

24:14.931 --> 24:17.586
- No, but I found out
where the money's coming from.

24:18.805 --> 24:21.677
The seed money originated
in this bank in The Hague.

24:21.721 --> 24:23.853
It's been on the
Financial Action Task Force's

24:23.897 --> 24:25.855
watchlist for years.

24:25.899 --> 24:27.640
- So they suspect
the bank that provides

24:27.683 --> 24:29.685
the seed money
for Marguerite Corporation

24:29.729 --> 24:31.731
is involved in international
money laundering?

24:31.774 --> 24:33.863
- I called them early this
morning, and they confirmed

24:33.907 --> 24:35.952
that the funding for the
Marguerite Corporation

24:35.996 --> 24:37.824
is coming
from the Russian mafia.

24:40.479 --> 24:42.524
- The Russian mafia
is behind all this?

24:42.568 --> 24:44.700
- Mm-hmm.

24:44.744 --> 24:46.485
- We need the name
of the boss.

24:46.528 --> 24:47.790
- I know. I'm still looking.

24:47.834 --> 24:49.531
- Will and Marianne
are running scared.

24:49.575 --> 24:50.750
They know we're after them.

24:50.793 --> 24:52.099
This boss is gonna
be looking for them too.

24:52.142 --> 24:54.188
- We gotta make sure
we find them first.

24:54.231 --> 25:01.456
♪

25:03.937 --> 25:05.068
- Hey.

25:07.549 --> 25:09.551
Rachel, come here. Rachel.

25:09.595 --> 25:11.727
- Why?

25:11.771 --> 25:13.555
- Hey! Stop and identify--

25:13.599 --> 25:15.557
- Rachel, Rachel, come here!
Oh, my God, Rachel!

25:15.601 --> 25:17.864
[screaming]

25:17.907 --> 25:20.214
- You are coming with me.

25:20.257 --> 25:21.824
We are going for a ride.

25:21.868 --> 25:24.174
- [screaming] Let me go!
- Shut up.

25:24.218 --> 25:26.655
- I want my mama!
- Get in.

25:26.699 --> 25:27.743
- Mommy!

25:27.787 --> 25:29.092
I want my mommy!

25:29.136 --> 25:30.703
- Shut up.

25:37.274 --> 25:38.319
- I can't believe
I let this happen.

25:38.362 --> 25:39.407
- This is not your fault.

25:39.450 --> 25:41.278
You did everything right.

25:41.322 --> 25:43.585
Those men are the
only ones to blame, okay?

25:43.629 --> 25:46.588
- Rachel was crying
for her mama.

25:46.632 --> 25:48.721
- Natalie, if you can
remember anything

25:48.764 --> 25:50.418
about the men that took her.

25:50.461 --> 25:51.941
Anything.

25:51.985 --> 25:55.205
- They were driving
a long black car.

25:55.249 --> 25:57.033
They had really nice suits.

25:57.077 --> 25:59.601
Their shoes were polished.

25:59.645 --> 26:01.081
And their accents.

26:01.124 --> 26:03.039
- Russian?

26:03.083 --> 26:04.388
- How did you know?

26:04.432 --> 26:08.610
[suspenseful music]

26:08.654 --> 26:10.394
- I promise you,
we are going to do

26:10.438 --> 26:13.354
everything we can
to find Rachel.

26:13.397 --> 26:15.356
- You know who took her?

26:15.399 --> 26:22.102
♪

26:22.145 --> 26:23.494
[phone dings]

26:25.322 --> 26:26.585
- Oh, my God.
- What?

26:26.628 --> 26:27.716
- Oh, my God, no, no, no.
- What is it?

26:27.760 --> 26:30.980
- Turn around right now.
Turn around!

26:31.024 --> 26:32.634
- Is this some kind of joke?
- He doesn't joke.

26:32.678 --> 26:34.418
He's got our baby, Will,
and now he knows

26:34.462 --> 26:36.116
we lied to protect her.

26:37.334 --> 26:39.119
We have to go back
or he'll kill her.

26:39.162 --> 26:41.643
- All we ever wanted was
to get away from this life.

26:41.687 --> 26:43.166
The robbery
forced us to improvise,

26:43.210 --> 26:44.341
but we can get away now.

26:44.385 --> 26:46.082
- Without our daughter?

26:46.126 --> 26:47.475
When I swore
to get her out of this life

26:47.518 --> 26:49.390
so they couldn't get their
hands on her, I meant it.

26:49.433 --> 26:52.306
- If we go back there,
he'll kill us.

26:52.349 --> 26:54.395
- My life doesn't matter
without Rachel.

26:56.310 --> 26:57.746
Turn around.

26:57.790 --> 26:59.400
Right now.

27:01.445 --> 27:05.101
Will, turn around.

27:05.145 --> 27:07.713
[suspenseful music]

27:07.756 --> 27:14.589
♪

27:18.680 --> 27:20.203
- What's the matter, Ortiz,

27:20.247 --> 27:22.249
you afraid of a
courthouse basement?

27:22.292 --> 27:24.077
- I'm afraid
of small town bureaucracies

27:24.120 --> 27:25.644
that refuse to digitize.

27:25.687 --> 27:28.211
- I think it's exciting.
I never get to go analog.

27:31.388 --> 27:35.305
Connelly, Constantine, Conway.

27:35.349 --> 27:37.351
You take Will,
I'll take Marianne.

27:39.875 --> 27:42.399
- All right,
I got Will's DMV file.

27:43.662 --> 27:45.359
Parking tickets.

27:45.402 --> 27:47.317
Voter registration,
Independent.

27:47.361 --> 27:49.189
- I don't think you
can be Independent

27:49.232 --> 27:51.713
if the Russian Mafia
have got their claws into you.

27:51.757 --> 27:53.628
- This goes back three decades.

27:53.672 --> 27:55.282
- Same with Marianne.

27:55.325 --> 27:57.414
I've even got
her marriage license here.

27:57.458 --> 27:59.765
They got married
right in this courthouse.

27:59.808 --> 28:01.810
- What's that?
- What's what?

28:03.203 --> 28:04.421
- Can you hold that up
to the light?

28:07.598 --> 28:09.078
See that writing?

28:13.692 --> 28:15.563
- Oh, my God,
this is from the '80s.

28:15.606 --> 28:18.435
- It's a petition
for a name change.

28:18.479 --> 28:22.091
- Before Marianne Mercer
was Marianne Conway,

28:22.135 --> 28:24.180
she was born
Marianne Matrushok.

28:24.224 --> 28:27.183
Her father initiated the
Americanization of her name

28:27.227 --> 28:28.881
because Marianne was born here,
she's an American citizen.

28:28.924 --> 28:30.491
- What about her father?

28:30.534 --> 28:33.494
- First generation Russian
immigrant Vasily Matrushok.

28:33.537 --> 28:35.583
[suspenseful music]

28:35.626 --> 28:38.151
- I think we just
found our Russian mob boss.

28:38.194 --> 28:40.414
- And the resident
pelmeni king.

28:40.457 --> 28:47.464
♪

28:50.293 --> 28:51.468
- I'm home.

28:55.690 --> 28:58.171
I know you understand me, Olga.

28:58.214 --> 29:00.782
- [speaking Russian]

29:06.527 --> 29:08.616
[line trills]
- Da?

29:08.659 --> 29:12.794
- Marina is here. Okay.

29:12.838 --> 29:14.274
- Your father
will see you now.

29:14.317 --> 29:21.324
♪

29:35.338 --> 29:36.687
- Papa.

29:43.346 --> 29:45.696
[sobbing]
Please forgive me.

29:48.351 --> 29:50.527
I should have told you
you had a granddaughter,

29:50.571 --> 29:52.312
but I was frightened.

29:54.575 --> 29:57.404
I have great pride
in our business,

29:57.447 --> 29:59.275
but it's so dangerous.

30:01.364 --> 30:03.845
I am ashamed to say
that I had hoped

30:03.889 --> 30:07.762
and wished to raise Rachel
away from it.

30:07.806 --> 30:09.416
Away from her family.

30:10.983 --> 30:14.943
But that doesn't mean
I ever stopped loving you.

30:16.902 --> 30:19.600
Please, Papa.

30:19.643 --> 30:22.385
[speaking Russian]

30:22.429 --> 30:25.649
Please just give me
my daughter back.

30:28.739 --> 30:31.568
- Oh, Solnyshko.

30:31.612 --> 30:33.309
You stop this.

30:33.353 --> 30:34.876
Stop this.

30:37.923 --> 30:38.880
Listen.

30:41.535 --> 30:43.493
There's so much you don't know.

30:43.537 --> 30:44.930
- I don't need to know.

30:44.973 --> 30:47.019
I just want my daughter back.

30:47.062 --> 30:49.717
- I don't have her, dear girl.

30:49.760 --> 30:51.327
- But-but--

30:53.373 --> 30:55.592
But you ordered me
to come back.

30:57.551 --> 30:59.727
- This isn't me.

30:59.770 --> 31:02.817
I've been too ashamed
to tell you.

31:02.861 --> 31:05.254
I don't give the orders
anymore.

31:08.344 --> 31:10.738
- Then who does?

31:13.872 --> 31:15.786
- All these toys for you.

31:15.830 --> 31:17.397
- But I'm not a baby.

31:17.440 --> 31:19.007
- Then why do you cry like one?

31:19.051 --> 31:26.275
♪

31:27.711 --> 31:29.278
- Hello, Rachel.

31:30.976 --> 31:32.455
I'm your Aunt Laura.

31:34.718 --> 31:36.764
Welcome to your new home.

31:36.807 --> 31:43.597
♪

31:59.221 --> 32:00.527
- Vasily Matrushok,
Russian mafia boss.

32:00.570 --> 32:03.008
He launders Russian money
through cash businesses.

32:03.051 --> 32:06.837
Everything from waxing centers
to off-track ponies

32:06.881 --> 32:08.970
to his various
marijuana operatives.

32:09.014 --> 32:10.972
- Vasily must have
set Marianne and Will up

32:11.016 --> 32:12.931
with seed money
for their grow operation,

32:12.974 --> 32:14.976
and I'm assuming it turned
a profit pretty fast.

32:15.020 --> 32:16.586
- Profit they keep
off the IRS grid

32:16.630 --> 32:18.110
like their true identities.

32:18.153 --> 32:19.589
- Well, how's that possible
when you have a child

32:19.633 --> 32:20.895
like Will and Marianne do?

32:20.939 --> 32:22.505
- Could be as easy
as bribing a clerk

32:22.549 --> 32:24.377
to delete her daughter's
birth certificate

32:24.420 --> 32:26.988
from vital records,
keep Rachel safe from Vasily.

32:27.032 --> 32:29.077
- And it worked up until
the Conways murdered Victor,

32:29.121 --> 32:30.252
Lupe, and their other
four employees

32:30.296 --> 32:31.384
that tried to rob them.

32:31.427 --> 32:32.559
- All right,
this is Vasily's place.

32:32.602 --> 32:34.256
We breach, we find Rachel.

32:34.300 --> 32:37.433
Just remember, he's not
going down without a fight.

32:37.477 --> 32:41.133
[tense music]

32:41.176 --> 32:46.181
♪

32:46.225 --> 32:48.096
All right, let's go.

33:09.030 --> 33:11.337
FBI, don't move!
Don't move, don't move!

33:11.380 --> 33:12.642
We got one in the corner.
Stand up.

33:12.686 --> 33:14.035
- Get your hands up now!
- Hands up!

33:14.079 --> 33:15.471
- Show me your hands!
- Higher!

33:15.515 --> 33:17.996
[indistinct shouting]

33:20.694 --> 33:22.522
All right, sit down. Sit down.

33:24.437 --> 33:26.482
- Marianne was here.

33:26.526 --> 33:32.097
She is gone now, and as far as
my granddaughter, I don't know.

33:32.140 --> 33:34.099
- Wrong--you're the one
who ordered your thugs

33:34.142 --> 33:36.144
to kidnap her,
all to punish your daughter.

33:36.188 --> 33:37.493
Where is she?

33:37.537 --> 33:40.192
- I would
never punish Marianne.

33:40.235 --> 33:42.237
She is my favorite.

33:42.281 --> 33:44.196
- You got a funny way
of showing it.

33:46.241 --> 33:49.505
- I was thrilled to learn
that Marianne

33:49.549 --> 33:51.072
had given me a granddaughter.

33:51.116 --> 33:53.466
I have yet to meet
little Rachel,

33:53.509 --> 33:55.946
but I am hopeful that one day,

33:55.990 --> 33:59.385
she and I will be close
like Marianne and I were.

33:59.428 --> 34:02.170
- You say you love
your granddaughter.

34:02.214 --> 34:03.780
If you don't have her,
someone else does,

34:03.824 --> 34:07.088
and that person might not have
a reason to keep her alive.

34:07.132 --> 34:10.961
- Yes, she will kill her,
most truly.

34:11.005 --> 34:12.137
- Who's "she"?

34:14.356 --> 34:17.446
- Marianne is a good mother,
I'm sure of it.

34:17.490 --> 34:20.014
She was always devoted, loving.

34:20.058 --> 34:22.060
But her sister, Laura...

34:22.103 --> 34:23.539
- Laura, the professor?

34:23.583 --> 34:28.631
- Laura, who forced me out
of my own pelmeni kingdom.

34:28.675 --> 34:31.939
Laura,
who gives the orders now.

34:36.509 --> 34:39.555
I told Marianne as much
before she left.

34:39.599 --> 34:41.427
- Did she say where
she was going?

34:42.776 --> 34:43.951
- No.

34:45.126 --> 34:45.953
- You're lying.

34:48.999 --> 34:50.566
- Young lady,
you're asking me to choose

34:50.610 --> 34:53.047
between my daughter
and the truth.

34:54.570 --> 34:56.268
Do I look like a fool?

34:58.096 --> 35:00.141
- Stand up.

35:00.185 --> 35:01.316
Get up.

35:01.360 --> 35:03.013
Hands behind your back.

35:03.057 --> 35:05.233
You're under arrest
for aiding and abetting.

35:05.277 --> 35:06.974
Let's go.

35:09.019 --> 35:11.370
- I know you have my daughter.
I'm coming for her now.

35:11.413 --> 35:13.589
- How nice of you to warn me.

35:13.633 --> 35:16.592
- That wasn't a warning.
It was a threat.

35:16.636 --> 35:19.247
- Mommy? Is that you?

35:19.291 --> 35:21.249
- Hi, bunny cat.

35:21.293 --> 35:24.209
Yeah, it's Mama.
I'm coming for you now.

35:24.252 --> 35:26.472
- We'll be waiting for you.

35:26.515 --> 35:28.430
- Tell me where
and what you want.

35:28.474 --> 35:31.346
- Ask Will, he'll know.

35:36.046 --> 35:38.005
- What is she talking about?

35:39.789 --> 35:42.575
- All I ever wanted
was to help this family.

35:42.618 --> 35:44.142
To give us an insurance policy.

35:44.185 --> 35:45.491
- The seeds
are our insurance policy.

35:47.232 --> 35:49.756
Will, tell me what
she's talking about right now.

35:53.194 --> 35:56.110
- Okay, the Vermont
State Police say

35:56.154 --> 35:57.546
no one's home
at Laura Mercer's house.

35:57.590 --> 35:58.678
- You talk to Middlebury?

35:58.721 --> 36:00.245
- They had no idea
who she really is.

36:00.288 --> 36:02.203
- The BOLO just popped
on Laura's car.

36:02.247 --> 36:04.249
She got a parking ticket
in downtown Montpelier.

36:04.292 --> 36:07.208
It's outside a commercial
building owned by Will Mercer.

36:07.252 --> 36:08.731
The tenant is Cox Press,
but I called

36:08.775 --> 36:10.646
the Vermont Secretary
of State's office.

36:10.690 --> 36:13.649
Cox Press filed for bankruptcy
five years ago.

36:13.693 --> 36:15.216
- Well, if it's no longer
a printing company,

36:15.260 --> 36:16.826
what's Will using it for?

36:16.870 --> 36:19.699
No idea, but it's our best bet
where our fugitives will be.

36:22.223 --> 36:24.225
- I used the seeds
to grow these.

36:24.269 --> 36:27.228
And I hired the extra four
workers to tend the plants.

36:27.272 --> 36:29.317
It's a real insurance policy.

36:29.361 --> 36:31.101
I knew you wanted
to get away from your family,

36:31.145 --> 36:33.321
but I also knew if I told you,
when you found out about it

36:33.365 --> 36:34.801
you would be afraid
of the repercussions.

36:34.844 --> 36:36.411
- My father
would never hurt me

36:36.455 --> 36:38.631
because I would never
betray him, unlike you.

36:38.674 --> 36:41.329
- You were always
Papa's favorite.

36:41.373 --> 36:42.765
- You set the bar low.

36:42.809 --> 36:45.638
- He forgave too easy.
He grew soft in his old age.

36:45.681 --> 36:47.205
I had no choice
but to take over

36:47.248 --> 36:48.728
for the good of our family.

36:48.771 --> 36:50.338
- The family
you're now ruining.

36:50.382 --> 36:52.166
- The family I'm protecting.

36:52.210 --> 36:53.820
You've been keeping secrets.

36:53.863 --> 36:55.387
As soon as
I learned about Rachel,

36:55.430 --> 36:57.519
I knew that there was more
you must be hiding.

36:57.563 --> 36:59.695
Because to betray the family,
to shut us out,

36:59.739 --> 37:01.567
there had to be a pattern.

37:03.264 --> 37:05.223
- And a secret grow operation

37:05.266 --> 37:07.834
worth more than the family
business twice over?

37:07.877 --> 37:09.618
A business that
should belong to me.

37:09.662 --> 37:10.837
- I didn't know
about this place

37:10.880 --> 37:12.882
until I set foot
in here two minutes ago.

37:12.926 --> 37:15.145
You want this
whole grow operation, take it.

37:15.189 --> 37:16.538
The seeds? You can have them,

37:16.582 --> 37:17.800
That's what
you really want, right?

37:17.844 --> 37:19.280
- Honey, please--
- Shut up, you stupid

37:19.324 --> 37:20.847
son of a bitch
and let the women talk.

37:23.458 --> 37:25.721
- Mm, there's my Marianne.

37:25.765 --> 37:27.245
We have a deal.

37:30.335 --> 37:32.293
- Rachel?
- Mommy!

37:32.337 --> 37:33.599
- Mama's here.

37:33.642 --> 37:34.817
- The seeds.

37:34.861 --> 37:38.691
[tense music]

37:38.734 --> 37:40.388
And the rest?

37:40.432 --> 37:41.737
- You'll get them.

37:41.781 --> 37:43.348
- Mommy, help me!

37:43.391 --> 37:44.610
- You're coming with me--

37:44.653 --> 37:47.177
- Actually, I've taken
a shine to the girl.

37:47.221 --> 37:48.570
- You gave me your word.

37:48.614 --> 37:50.746
- I guess we're both liars.

37:50.790 --> 37:51.617
- No.

37:53.575 --> 37:55.403
- FBI, don't move!
- Drop the weapon!

37:55.447 --> 38:02.149
♪

38:04.543 --> 38:05.848
- Drop the weapon.

38:10.723 --> 38:11.767
Let the girl go.

38:11.811 --> 38:13.639
- Nyet!

38:18.774 --> 38:21.386
- I want my mommy.
- Come here. Come here.

38:26.652 --> 38:28.349
- Drop the weapon!

38:28.393 --> 38:29.698
Drop the weapon!

38:33.223 --> 38:34.660
Drop the weapon.

38:40.753 --> 38:42.668
- Rachel.

38:42.711 --> 38:43.930
- Clear.

38:46.715 --> 38:48.369
- You saved her life.

38:48.413 --> 38:49.762
Thank you.

38:49.805 --> 38:51.372
- I'm a mother too.

38:51.416 --> 38:53.243
I know what it's like
to be willing to do anything

38:53.287 --> 38:54.941
for your child.

38:54.984 --> 38:56.725
- Hands behind your back.

38:56.769 --> 38:58.640
- You're still going to prison.

38:58.684 --> 39:00.207
Come here, Rachel.

39:01.861 --> 39:04.690
- Mommy.
- It'll be okay.

39:07.519 --> 39:08.868
- Mommy.

39:11.784 --> 39:14.264
- And I realize I don't
have the physical need

39:14.308 --> 39:16.484
for maternity leave, but...

39:16.528 --> 39:18.704
I never took it with Anais.

39:18.747 --> 39:21.489
And Charlotte's working now,
and I feel like it's my turn.

39:21.533 --> 39:23.491
- You don't need
to justify wanting

39:23.535 --> 39:25.406
to spend time with your baby.

39:25.450 --> 39:28.278
The bureau has a clear policy
on maternity leave.

39:28.322 --> 39:29.802
You're entitled to take it.

39:33.327 --> 39:34.502
- Have you told the team yet?

39:34.546 --> 39:36.417
- They were all
very understanding.

39:38.767 --> 39:40.595
But I didn't tell them
the real reason I wanted

39:40.639 --> 39:41.901
to take this time.

39:44.730 --> 39:46.384
Jess's death.

39:47.515 --> 39:48.516
It scared me.

39:50.388 --> 39:52.520
And I don't want to look back
in twenty years' time

39:52.564 --> 39:54.740
and regret choosing work
over family,

39:54.783 --> 39:57.699
even if just
for a couple of months.

39:57.743 --> 39:59.266
Life's short.

39:59.309 --> 40:01.442
[somber music]

40:01.486 --> 40:04.010
You never know
how long you have.

40:04.053 --> 40:07.492
- Listen, I understand
that completely.

40:09.407 --> 40:12.714
What you just told me, Sheryll,
that is not weakness.

40:12.758 --> 40:13.933
That is strength.

40:13.976 --> 40:16.979
It's part of why
you are such a good agent

40:17.023 --> 40:19.417
and an even better person.

40:21.941 --> 40:24.422
I'll submit
that paperwork tomorrow.

40:26.815 --> 40:28.295
- Thank you.

40:29.601 --> 40:30.819
I appreciate it.

40:34.344 --> 40:36.825
- Ooh, what timing is this.

40:36.869 --> 40:38.305
- What is?

40:38.348 --> 40:40.568
- I just got an email from CID;
it's official.

40:40.612 --> 40:44.659
The new SSA has been
selected to run the task force.

40:46.444 --> 40:47.967
- Who is it?

40:48.010 --> 40:54.408
♪

41:02.024 --> 41:04.984
[dramatic music]

41:05.027 --> 41:12.034
♪

41:21.566 --> 41:23.350
[wolf howls]
